items.name: Bronze Statue LoRA
items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

To support me you can buy me a coffe at https://ko-fi.com/antonioriolo

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 10

  • LORA weight for txt2img: reccomended 0.3-0.7.

  • Keys: bronze_statue, in the middle of a square, sitting on a bench, riding a horse, on a pedestal

I made this model just for fun. It works as expected, it just makes a bronze_statue out of the subject.

I have tryied to use it with other LoRAs, like clothing LoRAs but it doesn't always work, sometime it does, so feel free to try your own LoRAs with it.

The training images are not only about humans, there are many about animals and fantasy stuff, so it should be able to generate a statue of everything, just give it a try maybe with a xy plot on the weights.

It also works with anime, example in the posted images.

Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.name: Sally Saint Ford - Macross 7
items.description:
Well another one of my planned or unplanned Macross 7 character. Here's is my favorite bridge bunny of the series. Probably some of the animators feels the same as she has comparatively more material than Millia's daughter Emilia(who has her own movie). Anyway as this is done, only Akiko and Rex remain to make use of all the screencaps I collected.

Had Good results with: <lora:SallySaintFord:0.7>, SallySaintFord, large_breasts,

There are 3 available outfits:

  • UNSUniform (Somehow it likes giving her pants. So I recommend using pencil_skirt with a low weight, pants in the negatives or both)

  • NoJacketUniform (in case of pants do the same as before)

  • SallyCivilianOutfit (might want to add jeans for more accuracy as it sometimes adds generic pants)

All in all I like it, other than the pants propensity issue it seems to work ok.

As This was trained I won't upload the dataset, in it's place is the tag summary which you can use to experiment.

items.name: Utopia
items.description:
Realistic anime girl illustrations inspired by early 20th century impressionism with pastel like colors.

It defaults to generating female characters with slim figures and has the capability to generate some nsfw content with focus in nude, semi-nude. (Use tags such as "mature" and "big breast" to get less slim female characters)

A lower CFG scale will give more creative illustrations with oil-paint like depictions.

When you use Hires.Fix, you'll get less saturated color and less texture.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Use of after detailer is recommended for better faces. ADetailer

To install ADetailer, within automatic1111, click (extensions -> install from URL -> paste GitHub link.)

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Settings I like using:

  • Clip Skip: 1~2

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M Karras *(or DPM++ SDE Karras)

  • Sample Steps: 25 *(10 for DPM++ SDE Karras)

  • GFG Scale: 3.5~7.5

  • ADetailer Model: face_yolov8m

  • ADetailer Mask Blur: 10~15

*(In my experience, the SDE produces more realistic and 3D like images compared to 2M. For the anime-illustration type style of this model, I personally think the 2M suits better.)

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Recommended Resolution:

  • 832x1248 (mixed)

  • 768x1152 (ok)

  • 640x960 (good)

  • 512x768 (great)

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Merged Models include:

BeenYou - B17 | Stable Diffusion Checkpoint | Civitai

ReV Animated - v1.2.2 | Stable Diffusion Checkpoint | Civitai

Hassaku (hentai model) - V1.1 | Stable Diffusion Checkpoint | Civitai

This LoRA is able to generate images with 2 girls on top of each other with their private parts closely together, hence the name "pussy sandwich" (I got it from danbooru tags).

You can use 1.0 weight or more and your preferred CFG.

You should use the trigger word pussy sandwich, but you also need to better describe the scene in you prompt, so you should also at least include some of the following: 2girls, looking back, from behind, ass, pussy, lying, yuri, etc.

Since we're talking about stable diffusion, it may not work 100% of the times, even with the above settings, but you can always try to increase the weight of the lora, or the weight of key tags in the prompt to help with the effect, e.g. (2girls:1.2), as it sometimes can make it work. Using other loras works, but may be harder to obtain a good result, and you many need to try different seeds. (My example images using multiple loras are cherry-picked).

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

items.name: Angus McKie Style
items.description:
Angus McKie is a British artist known for his contributions to the science fiction and fantasy genres. He has worked as an illustrator, providing cover art and interior illustrations for numerous books, magazines, and comics.

McKie's artwork often features futuristic and fantastical scenes, depicting otherworldly landscapes, spacecraft, and imaginative creatures. He has a distinctive style characterized by his attention to detail, vibrant colors, and a sense of depth and atmosphere in his compositions.

One of McKie's notable works is his collaboration with writer Michael Moorcock on the "Dancers at the End of Time" series, where he created stunning cover illustrations that captured the surreal and decadent nature of the stories.

In addition to his illustrations, McKie has also worked in the field of animation, contributing his artistic talents to projects such as the animated film "Heavy Metal" (1981). He has also created concept art for video games, adding his unique vision to the visual development of digital worlds.

McKie's artwork combines elements of science fiction and fantasy, often blurring the boundaries between the two genres. His ability to create intricate and captivating imagery has made him a respected figure in the realm of speculative art.

Angus McKie's illustrations have left a lasting impact on the science fiction and fantasy community. His imaginative artwork transports viewers to extraordinary realms, evoking a sense of wonder and igniting the imagination. With his contributions to literature, comics, animation, and gaming, McKie's art continues to inspire and captivate fans of the genre.

items.name: GlassTech - World Morph
items.description:
GlassTech - World Morph 💎

This is my second attempt at creating a world lora following the "Konyconi-LoRA" method, if you don't know Konyconi you should really check out his LoRAs they're simply mindblowing 🤯

About : this LoRA "GlassTech" is meant to influence or change the entire course of the final image to a dimension that relies solely on: glass ,glass circuitry, synthetic glass, glass fiber ...

with that in mind you must use the trigger word glasstech then pick one of two directions:

  • Sci fi, by adding scifi to the prompt witch was my primary intent with LoRA.

  • Fantasy, by adding magic or fantasy the prompt witch mostly works well with architecture , armor or creatures giving them an arcane eleven look.

further more, you can include the one of the following decorators to influence the style even more : transparent iridescent gold wires

Usage Tips :

  • use weight of 0.7 to 0.9 to influence the image .

  • use weight of 1 to 1.5 to use as world morph .

  • adding transparent with scifi works rly well

  • use hires fix for large detailed scenes

  • Mostly use with "Eular a" with a step count over 20

  • rly shines at img2img at weights over 1

Samples workflow :

  1. add the LoRA at weight of 0.9 to the prompt along with glasstech scifi transparent

  2. set the sampler "Eular a" , steps 30 , CFG Scale 5.5

  3. enabled hires fix at 0.55 , steps 20 , Upscale by 1.5

  4. Generate, then send to img2img

  5. crank up the LoRA weight to 1.2 or 1.4, steps 35 , Denoising strength 0.42

  6. increase the resolution for example to 1024x1024 , then Generate

  7. send to extras for further upscaling if needed

have fun and consider rating ⭐

items.name: MysticTurducken
items.description:
This is a merge of, well, merges. It consists of several models provided by the Unstable Diffusion community, as well as one of my own. It was pretty much a yolo merge on my part to see what would come of it, but I've been happy with the results and received a lot of good feedback on it, so I'm posting it here for others to get a chance to play with it.

It has a slight human bias (consider the source; it's milder than I expected,) and it excels at abstract themes, backgrounds, somehow pixel art, and of course nsfw stuff. I haven't thoroughly explored the potential of this merge, as it's existed for just over a day now.

Known limitations:

  • Eyes are pretty messy when faces get to about the distance of a full-body shot. This is one of those models that needs a little hand-holding there, be it through highresfix, Ddetailer, or Adetailer.

  • Pixel art is surprisingly fantastic with this, but the effect tends to break down around the face where the model goes into a sort of tryhard mode and returns to its 2.5d roots. Adetailer or Ddetailer can be used to improve this case by using "pixelated" or "pixel art" in the prompt for either along with the usual face details you'd typically use with either tool.

  • Truly SFW content featuring women. While it is very possible to gen fully-clothed characters with this merge, you'll probably have to fight with the model to avoid things like excessive cleavage. While I tagged this model for mature themes only, it is entirely possible to use this solely for SFW purposes. You'll likely just find that harder to achieve than in other models that likely fit the task better.

  • Cats. You can get good cats on CLIP skip 2 and 3, but you probably won't be able to do so using a minimalist prompt without. Unfortunately, most of the style knowledge is in the outer layer, so that might be a pretty unadorned cat if you go that deep for it.

Components:

  • Senzubean's SenzusHolyshit merge (components unknown)

  • WildKeeper's WildsMix (components unknown)

  • My own HDDarkmode, which consists of

    • Hentai Diffusion epoch 17

    • JWST Deep Space Diffusion

    • Double Exposure Diffusion

    • Noise Offset For True Darkness in SD

    • My Kan Liu LoRA merged in at a low weight

      • Many of the components were added through block weighted merging early on, before things like recipe logging were added, so the exact details were lost to time like a day after I whammed the first parts of that together back in November.
